All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Activity
The Activity class represents an activity with a name, description, cost, capacity, signed-up passengers, and an associated destination.
ActivityManager
The ActivityManager class manages the sign-up process of passengers for activities.
ActivitySignUpStrategy
The ActivitySignUpStrategy interface defines the method for signing up a passenger for an activity.
Destination
The Destination class represents a destination with a name and a list of activities.
GoldSignUpStrategy
The GoldSignUpStrategy class implements the ActivitySignUpStrategy interface and provides a strategy for signing up gold passengers for activities.
Passenger
The Passenger class represents a passenger with a name, number, balance, signed-up activities, and a sign-up strategy.
PassengerFactory
The PassengerFactory class is responsible for creating instances of Passenger based on the type.
PremiumSignUpStrategy
The PremiumSignUpStrategy class implements the ActivitySignUpStrategy interface and provides a strategy for signing up premium passengers for activities.
Runner
The Runner class demonstrates the creation of a travel package with destinations, passengers, and activities.
StandardSignUpStrategy
The StandardSignUpStrategy class implements the ActivitySignUpStrategy interface and provides a strategy for signing up standard passengers for activities.
tIntegration
 
TravelPackage
The TravelPackage class represents a travel package that includes destinations, passengers, and activities.
